== The Five Elements and the Five Lights

Very humbly, I don't claim to be an expert on how the elements are actually mind lights, all I can do is do my best to use a very limited range of concepts and speech to convey this. The only reason why I would want to convey this, I'm going to reiterate that; please don't let this be a belief system or an idea that you conform to. This should be like something that when you're naturally abiding in your own mind, you start to see how the elements are correlating; they're co-emerging, they're related to your mind.

So, as you rest, and you leave that alone... oftentimes for example, when we do Tögal and we see this light phenomenon and the light rays, even just seeing orbs and rainbows and things like that. After I was introduced to Tögal for example, I was able to see rainbow light and light rays that I had not noticed before, for whatever reason.

Now, I know many people who don't have to go to a Tögal retreat, and yes, I'm talking about those little light rays that your phone can capture, but or our naked eyes sometimes, or I should say our mind, is not seeing that. Okay? For some reason, I was one of the ones who had to go through the retreat and be introduced to these teachings before I was able to see more light phenomenon. And then also, I think it was because, well there are many hidden blessings, but I think it was also because of the Trekchö. If you combine our awareness practice with Tögal, this is the ideal way.

And when you're just resting in awareness and your mind starts to soften the constructing, then you start to see one holistic mind here. And what we call the elements in our modern kind of language, which by the way, we only have about 1.5 million words (how many of those are science... scientific words, right?). And then each person only has, I think it's estimated only about 40,000 words that they know, and that could be quite less for some; more for others or course. So all I'm trying to say is that we have a boundary constraint here---we're constrained to our concepts, to our words about the elements.

What we call elements are really aspects of our mind, very powerful, subtle aspects. Just like in a dream: you're creating the earth, you're creating the buildings, and then you're walking around like, "Hey, that's a cool building." Well, your mind just created that building and you don't even know it, and it's sitting there holding the building in place for you like rebar or something, mental rebar. We have mental footers.

And yes, you could say that is the initial, the second link in the twelve links of dependent origination. That is fabrication. Okay? We are fabricating our environment, because what comes after fabrications? Name and form; consciousness. So, we start... this whole environment... there's a deep separation, we separate ourselves from the environment. Just like in a dream you walk around, "Nice building", you separated yourself from the building, didn't you? 

So as you're fabricating it... The third link of dependent origination is consciousness; so as you're fabricating that building, it's alive with your mind, isn't it? So the twelve links are actually not linear: they're interwoven. Then you see it and say, "That's a building"; you give it a name, and every time you see that name it will have a form with it: a square, a rectangle, vertical-rectangle.

And then your senses develop; you want to touch it, so you have contact, right? Yes. And so you're just walking around this whole dream, talking to people. That's a contact, okay? Which is that next link in dependent origination.

And then you have feeling; you have this imagined contact with the elements. And after feeling you have craving, clinging, becoming, birth, old age, sickness, and death, all based on our little world that we create.

So someone asked about sacred geometry. I think it's related, because awareness itself (the Dharmakaya), is like a womb of infinite potential, just like a mama. Really her womb can have many different kinds of children; especially if you look at the puppies, oh my gosh, so many different puppies come out of the mama dogs, right?

So just like that, there's a womb here of the infinite. And depending on causes and conditions that you check out like books from the library, you start to construct. So, the womb can be compared to the Flower of Life---I think so, I'm going to say that. I know I may suffer criticism for that, or some people may raise their eyebrows, but that's okay; I'm willing to jump on that limb.

And so, the Flower of Life then gets sown, and on top of the Flower of Life, the Sambhogakaya mixes into it, and that's Metatron's Cube which you hear about. If you've ever looked in Metatron's Cube, you know that the mathematics for every single platonic shape, color---everything is there in Metatron's Cube; even formulas for our periodic table are found there, somehow. That's way beyond my studies, but…

So you have in sacred geometry, I do believe you have that masculine-feminine union for creation. Flower of Life: feminine; Metatron's Cube: the weaving into it is masculine; and then you have the child, which is all your fundamental particles and shapes, platonic solids, and various creations from that, right? So, good question; sacred geometry is one of the few things I would confidently plug into Dzogchen in a deeper way.

And you also see the Flower of Life by the way all over ancient temples, so. And they use the number 9 a lot. For example, the mala beads; there are 108 beads: 1+0+8 is what? 9. If you cut that in half, it's 54: 5+4 is 9. Cut that in half, 27: 2+7 is 9. Cut that in half, 13.5: 1+3+5 is 9. It keeps going infinitely, and they used to build their temples on this kind of infinite pattern. Nine has many more patterns in it, of course, right?

So I know there are some comments there, and they're long and they're tiny, and they've disappeared, so I hope I don't miss anything, but I'm just going to return to the chart here; I'm just setting the basis for this, okay?

